## Documentation Policy

**IMPORTANT**: Unless explicitly requested, **DO NOT create documentation files**.

This applies to:
- ❌ No summary documents (e.g., `IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md`, `UPDATE_SUMMARY.md`)
- ❌ No how-to guides or README files
- ❌ No reference documentation
- ❌ No changelog files
- ❌ No testing documentation

**Only create documentation when user specifically asks for it.**

**Exceptions:**
- ✅ Code comments (inline documentation is fine)
- ✅ XML documentation comments in code
- ✅ Updating existing documentation if asked to modify it

---

## BeFirst Portal Grid View Pattern

**CRITICAL**: When creating grid partial views in BeFirst Portal, ALWAYS use the MvcGrid pattern, NOT manual HTML tables.

### Correct Pattern (NonFactors.Mvc.Grid)

**Partial View** (`_GetXxxxList.cshtml`):
```cshtml
@using NonFactors.Mvc.Grid;

@model Firstronic.Core.Entities.App.Engineering.tbl_XXXX_FULL_partial

@(Html
      .Grid(Model.Items)        // or Model.Modelo
      .Build(columns =>
      {
        columns.Add(model => model.PropertyName).Titled("Column Header");
        columns.Add(model => Html.ActionLink("Delete", "DeleteXxxx", new { id = model.AutoID }, new { @class = "delRow" }));
      })
      .UsingSourceUrl(Url.Action("GetXxxxList", "ControllerName", new { id = Model.id }))
      .Empty("No data found")
      .Id("mvcXxxxList")
  )
```

**Controller Method**:
```csharp
[AcceptVerbs(HttpVerbs.Get | HttpVerbs.Post)]
[Authorize(Roles = "BF Administrator,BF Part Edit")]
public PartialViewResult GetXxxxList(int id)
{
  var model = new tbl_XXXX_FULL_partial();
  model.id = id;

  SqlParameter[] idParameters = new SqlParameter[]{
    new SqlParameter("@Id", SqlDbType.Int){ Value = id }
  };

  string query = @"SELECT ... FROM ... WHERE PartID = @Id";

  model.Items = db.Database.SqlQuery<Firstronic.Core.Entities.App.Engineering.tbl_XXXX_FULL>(query, idParameters)
                  .ToArray()
                  .ToList()
                  .AsQueryable();

  return PartialView("_GetXxxxList", model);
}

// Wrapper model with id + Items/Modelo
public class tbl_XXXX_FULL_partial
{
  public int id { get; set; }
  public IQueryable<Firstronic.Core.Entities.App.Engineering.tbl_XXXX_FULL> Items { get; set; }
}
```

**Entity Model** (in Firstronic.Core.Entities.App.Engineering namespace):
```csharp
namespace Firstronic.Core.Entities.App.Engineering
{
  public class tbl_XXXX_FULL
  {
    public int AutoID { get; set; }
    // ... other properties matching SQL query columns
  }
}
```

**Key Points**:
- ✅ Use `@using NonFactors.Mvc.Grid;`
- ✅ Model is `tbl_XXXX_FULL_partial` with `id` + `Items`/`Modelo` properties
- ✅ Use `Html.Grid(Model.Items).Build(columns => {...})`
- ✅ Use `.UsingSourceUrl()` for AJAX reload
- ✅ Use `.Empty()` for no-data message
- ✅ Use `.Id()` for grid HTML ID
- ✅ Use `Html.ActionLink()` with CSS class for delete actions
- ✅ Query returns `IQueryable<tbl_XXXX_FULL>` via `.ToArray().ToList().AsQueryable()`
- ❌ NEVER create manual `<table>` HTML
- ❌ NEVER use `IEnumerable<dynamic>` as model
- ❌ NEVER use `@model` other than the `_FULL_partial` wrapper

